{"key":"processedPost-17163867","value":{"id":17163867,"first":17163384,"last":17163867,"when":1352119257,"utime":"11/05/12 02:40 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /> Can I just put them all in the oven at just under 200F? How long should they be in for? I'm not sure if this makes a difference in how long they'll take to pasteurize if left in the oven, but there are enough jars to fill it (wall to wall, 3 or 4 stacks).</blockquote><br />No.&nbsp; You need to sterilize and that requires steam to prevent the substrate drying out.&nbsp; It can't be done in an oven because when the inside of the jars reaches the boiling point, all the moisture will escape through the lid and inoculation/gas exchange holes.<br /><a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">Follow the brf tek</a>.&nbsp; It sounds like you need to make a run to the store for a large pot with a tight fitting lid as shown in the video.<br />RR","title":"Re: Pasteurizing jars in oven?"}}